This is a Coq formalisation of the Zermelo-Fraenkel set theory 
(aka ZF Set Theory) loosely based on the book:

Gaisi Takeuti, Wilson M. Zaring, Introduction to Axiomatic Set Theory,
Graduate Texts in Mathematics, Second Edition, Springer-Verlag, 1981.

Current Hermes workflow:
1. Find the next proposition.
2. Update the next proposition cache.
3. Choose the location.
4. Choose the local name.
5. Update the next proposition cache.
6. Read the book proof/outline if present.
7. Design and explain my own proof/API outline.
8. Audit the formal API against that outline.
9. Implement the agreed plan.
10. Code review checkpoint.
11. Update the shared current page state.
12. Update the shared last proposition state.
13. Loop back to item 1.

 
